Summary:
licensed banks may reschedule the credit facilities of eligible borrowers for a maximum period up to ten years. Licensed banks shall establish a Relief Banking Unit for the purpose of extending and monitoring the relief measures under the cited Circular for the effective implementation of such relief measures. The existing Business Revival Units established under Circular No. 02 of 2024 on Guidelines for the Establishment of Business Revival units in Licensed Banks, will continue for the intended purpose thereof. The banks are requested to establish a transparent grievance-handling mechanism with respect to any dispute that may arise between the bank and the borrower on the valuation of auctioned properties. [Limited Sharing]# Bank Name Annexure A Reporting as at Total Amount Considered for Rescheduling (Rs. 000s) Tenor of the Rescheduled Loan Applicable Interest Rate on Reschedule Loan (%) Agreed Date of Commencement of Repayment (DD/MM/YYYY) Has the Repayments Commenced (Yes/No) Outstanding Charges or Fees as at the Date of Reschedul ed Loan ( Rs. '000s) Charges or fees Waived off by the banks on rescheduling by the Banks on reschuling ( Rs.-'000s). Reschedules Loan for the Capital Reschedilled Loan forThe Interest If Reschediled Serial No. 04 of 2024 from 15.12.2024 to the Reporting Date Date of Classifying to Stage 3 (DD-MM/yy YY) Facility Number Borrower Name Amount Outstanding as at 15. 12. 2024. If Rejected, Reasons for Rejection Interest (Rs-'000's)

